cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper is about abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses using machine learning techniques, such as transfer learning and data synthesis, to improve performance, which suggests that it could also fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models using metrics such as ROUGE, which is commonly used in information retrieval (IR) research, suggesting that it could also fit into cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
